Experiment 2
(Flow Control)
1.	To show the largest number among three.
2.	To show the student ‘Ram ‘is securing mark below the pass mark 30.
3.	To show the lists of prime numbers from 0 to user input.
4.	To show that number is Armstrong number or not (for n numbers).
5.	To show that number is palindrome or not.
6.	To show the Fibonacci series from 0 to user input.
7.	Python program to find the factorial of a number provided by the user.
(Function)
8.	Python program to find the H.C.F of two input number.
9.	Python Program to find the L.C.M. of two input number.
10.	Python Program to find the factors of a number.
11.	To find the area of circle, square, rectangle, triangle and sphere.
(Files)
12.	Write a Python program to read an entire text file
13.	Write a Python program to read first n lines of a file.
14.	Write a Python program to append text to a file and display the text.
15.	Write a Python program to read last n lines of a file.
16.	Write a Python program to read a file line by line and store it into a list.
17.	Write a Python program to read a file line by line store it into a variable.
18.	Write a Python program to read a file line by line store it into an array.
19.	Write a python program to find the longest words.
20.	Write a Python program to count the number of lines in a text file.
21.	Write a Python program to count the frequency of words in a file.
22.	Write a Python program to get the file size of a plain file.
23.	Write a Python program to write a list to a file.
24.	Write a Python program to copy the contents of a file to another file.
25.	Write a Python program to combine each line from first file with the corresponding line in second file.
26.	Write a Python program to read a random line from a file.
27.	Write a Python program to assess if a file is closed or not.
28.	Write a Python program to remove newline characters from a file.
